definitions.definition: To confer with others in order to come to terms or reach an agreement .
To arrange or settle something by mutual agreement .
examples: We negotiated the contract to everyone's satisfaction.
The client and server computers must first negotiate a network protocol to be used.

definitions.definition: To succeed in coping with, getting over or navigate a hazard or obstacle.
examples: We negotiated the mountain track with difficulty.
Although the car was quite rickety, he could negotiate the curves very well.

definitions.definition: To transfer to another person with all the rights of the original holder; to pass , as a bill .
To transact business ; to carry on trade .

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To confer with others in order to come to terms or reach an agreement .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To arrange or settle something by mutual agreement .
( transitive ) To succeed in coping with, getting over or navigate a hazard or obstacle.
( transitive ) To transfer to another person with all the rights of the original holder; to pass , as a bill .
( obsolete ) To transact business ; to carry on trade .
